description: We create our Campbells® Condensed soups by adding less water right from the start, so theres more room for flavor. Not only do we have your favorite classic flavors, like Chicken Noodle, Tomato and Cream of Mushroom, but were always coming up with new flavors and varieties to delight your senses. Then it is finished with fresh organic cream from local Oregon dairies and a touch of garlic. Simple, yet so delicious! At Pacific Foods, we believe that making foods we're proud of is as much about the ingredients we use as it is about the actual recipe. We steer clear of additives, preservatives and common allergens, and avoid GMOs. The way we see it, nature knows how foods should taste, and we just try to follow her lead.

description: Campbell's® Homestyle soup is the soup that takes you home.Campbell's® Homestyle soups start with vegetables that are farm grown, and the soups have no preservatives added. Each recipe takes inspiration from homemade soup. When preparing Campbell's® Homestyle Chicken Noodle, we start with the whole chicken breasts and slice them up into juicy strips of white meat chicken. Our chicken meat is then oven roasted and added to a savory broth made from real chicken stock. With our Homestyle New England Clam Chowder, we source clams off the Atlantic coast and then add them to a creamy broth chocked with vegetables. description:
Est. 1982. Bring the taste of Louisiana home! Louisiana Fish Fry products family owned & operated.

Directions:
3 Easy Steps: 1. Melt 5 tbsp butter or margarine in sauce pan. Add mix. Stir over low heat until medium brown. 2. Add 2 cups water and 1 lb peeled crawfish tails or shrimp. Cover and bring to a boil. Stir often. 3. After mixture comes to a boil, reduce heat to low and cook 15 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes. Serve over rice and enjoy! Also great served over pasta. Variations: Instead of crawfish or shrimp, try our Etouffee mix using pre-cooked diced chicken, turkey or venison.
